The paper proposes a new class of orthogonal circulant matrices for compressed sensing, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of coherence parameter for uniform and non-uniform recovery, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of discrete-cosine transform (DCT) domain, which is a common technique in image and video processing (cs.SI).
